	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories  HIGHWAY Skating is a registered sporting club affiliated to Roller Sport SA. The club started in 2014 with a small group skating in Junior Roller Derby. Since then they have concentrated on developing the artistic roller-skating skills. In 2015 a team of eight skaters competed in the South African National Roller Skating Championships where they came second. Highway Skating is a fun Roller skating club for all ages offering roller skate lessons on Saturday mornings at Watercrest Mall Parking 2 and social midday and evening sessions. Bring your own skates or hire ours, but do come and experience the freedom of Rollerskating.         For more information www.highwayskat ing.co.za or call Catherine on 084 032 3686.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  